'''Giorgi "Gigi" Ugulava''' (Georgian: გიგი უგულავა) (born August 15, 1975) is a Georgian politician and the former Mayor of Tbilisi (2005–2013). He was one of the former leaders of the United National Movement (UNM) party and former close ally of the former President of Georgia Mikheil Saakashvili. On 10 February 2020, he was sentenced to 3 years in prison .[1] However, on May 15, President Salome Zourabichvili pardoned Ugulava.
